i ∈ [1, 4 − nw + 1] , j ∈ 1, nt + 2 − nf + 1 , k ∈ [1, nconv1] ,
where bconv1 is the bias vector, f is a relu function (Nair and Hinton, 2010), and nt = nl + nd + nm. Zconv1,k i, j is the element at the ith row and jth column of the kth feature map Zconv1,k.
Pooling layer We apply the max pooling to extract the robust features from the feature maps Zconv1. ng and np are the length and width of a ﬁlter of pooling layer, respectively. The pooling outputs of all the feature maps are Zconvpool1,
Zconvpool1,k i, j = Max Zconv1,k i : i + ng , j : j + np , (4)

