(12)

where z ∈ R2 is the classiﬁcation label vector and T is a set of training samples. If l1 is associated with d2, the second dimension of the vector z is 1 and the ﬁrst one is 0. On the contrary, if l1 is not associated with d2, the ﬁrst dimension of z is 1 and the second one is 0.
We denote all neural network parameters by θ . The objective function in our learning process is deﬁned as follows,

